    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-18T21:18:10+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-18T21:18:10+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T11:48:10Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T11:48:10Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system south of the Bight will drift to the south east while a trough extends across western coasts late on Thursday. This trough will linger along the coastline into Friday, developing into the cold front that will clear into the east early Saturday. A high pressure system will begin to move in from the west on Saturday, cross the Bight, slowly drifting to eastern SA by Monday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-18T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Slight chance of a shower about the Gammon Ranges, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Yunta, slight chance elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h tending west to southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h during the morning then becoming westerly 15 to 25 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Leigh Creek, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h tending south to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower about the Gammon Ranges, near zero chance elsewhere. The chance of morning frost south of Yunta. Winds southerly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-22T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-23T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-21T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-22T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. Patches of morning frost south of Leigh Creek. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then tending south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
